info:
Responsibilities：
1. Collecting copycat and counterfeits clues and maintain the data status.
2. Formatting contract templates.
3. Legal research, especially concerning labor/anti-unfair competition/commercial bribery law/regulation;
4. Legal watch, provide latest legislation regarding the above topics;
5. Case study concerning the above topics, and provide legal analysis;
6. Review/draft of simple contracts, including contracts comparison; Contract management;
7. Translation of legal documents;
8. On-site consultation of corporate registration related matters;
9. Other task as assigned.

Requirements：
1. Major in law; 
2. Passed national bar examination is preferred; 
3. Good command of written English; 
4. Strong sense of responsibility and commitment; 
5. Good at communicating with others; 
6. Good at excel and data analysis.
7. Minimum 3 months internship, long-term commitment is preferred.

•	Work closely with the training managers to understand their needs and requirements;
•	To be responsible to arrange all the logistics for the training programme with minimum supervision from training managers (such as collect the course enrolment, arrange the course materials, monitor the course attendance, collect the course feedback, and arrange air-tickets and hotel for the trainers);
•	Answer enquiries from internal users, including partners;
•	To prepare various course related reports;
•	To monitor the course actual expenditure VS budget;
•	To provide inputs to the programs arrangements;
•	Other ad-hoc tasks: data organization, PPT creation and enhancement, etc.
•	Commit to working at least 4 days per week.
•	Based at Kampus
